abstract: Long-delayed initial results of the September election show President Ashraf Ghani leading with a slight majority of the vote.
snippet: Long-delayed initial results of the September election show President Ashraf Ghani leading with a slight majority of the vote.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan was on course to win a second five-year term, the country’s election commission announced Sunday, based on long-delayed preliminary results of the September vote, which has faced protests and accusations of fraud.

abstract: Croatia's conservative president will face a liberal former prime minister in a runoff election early next month after no candidate won an outright majority in a first round of voting Sunday, near-complete results showed.
snippet: Croatia's conservative president will face a liberal former prime minister in a runoff election early next month after no candidate won an outright majority in a first round of voting Sunday, near-complete results showed.
lead_paragraph: ZAGREB, Croatia — Croatia's conservative president will face a liberal former prime minister in a runoff election early next month after no candidate won an outright majority in a first round of voting Sunday, near-complete results showed.
headline_main: Croatia's Presidential Contest Heads to Jan. 5 Runoff Vote

abstract: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
snippet: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Was...
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
headline_main: North Korea's Kim Holds Military Meeting as Tension Rises Under Looming Deadline

abstract: For years, members of a secret team, Unit 29155, operated without Western security officials having any idea about their activities. But an attack on an arms dealer in Sofia helped blow their cover.
snippet: For years, members of a secret team, Unit 29155, operated without Western security officials having any idea about their activities. But an attack on an arms dealer in Sofia helped blow their cover.
lead_paragraph: SOFIA, Bulgaria — The Russian assassin used an alias, Sergei Fedotov, and slipped into Bulgaria unnoticed, checking into a hotel in Sofia near the office of a local arms manufacturer who had been selling ammunition to Ukraine.

headline_main: In France, Holiday Skating Rinks Are an Unlikely Climate Battleground
headline_print_headline: The Joys of Icy Strides,  Tempered by Concerns  Over Carbon Footprints

abstract: Since 2001, 23 public and private pools have appeared in Kabul, but only two allow women. They’re a welcome refuge from suicide bombings and the threat of a Taliban takeover.
snippet: Since 2001, 23 public and private pools have appeared in Kabul, but only two allow women. They’re a welcome refuge from suicide bombings and the threat of a Taliban takeover.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — When Fatema Saeedi is in the pool, she cannot hear the crowded, chaotic noise of the city around her. She does not think about suicide bombings or Taliban attacks. She concentrates on her breathing as she moves through the water. One hand in front of the other. Exhale.

abstract: North Korea said Sunday leader Kim Jong Un has convened a key ruling party meeting to decide on steps to bolster the country’s military capability.
snippet: North Korea said Sunday leader Kim Jong Un has convened a key ruling party meeting to decide on steps to bolster the country’s military capability.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — North Korea said Sunday leader Kim Jong Un has convened a key ruling party meeting to decide on steps to bolster the country’s military capability.
headline_main: N Korean Leader Holds Party Meeting to Bolster Military
headline_print_headline: N Korean Leader Holds Party Meeting to Bolster Military

abstract: Bolivian former President Evo Morales on Saturday appealed for his supporters to attend a rally on the border between Argentina and Bolivia on Dec. 29 to choose a candidate for Bolivia's  election early next year.
snippet: Bolivian former President Evo Morales on Saturday appealed for his supporters to attend a rally on the border between Argentina and Bolivia on Dec. 29 to choose a candidate for Bolivia's  election early next year.
lead_paragraph: La Paz (Reuters) - Bolivian former President Evo Morales on Saturday appealed for his supporters to attend a rally on the border between Argentina and Bolivia on Dec. 29 to choose a candidate for Bolivia's election early next year.
headline_main: Boliva's Ex-President Morales Plans Party Rally on Argentina Border
headline_print_headline: Boliva's Ex-President Morales Plans Party Rally on Argentina Border

abstract: The spectre of new confrontation between Pyongyang and Washington hangs over meetings between China, Japan and South Korea this week, with growing risks North Korean actions could end an uneasy detente and upend recent diplomatic efforts.
snippet: The spectre of new confrontation between Pyongyang and Washington hangs over meetings between China, Japan and South Korea this week, with growing risks North Korean actions could end an uneasy detente and upend recent diplomatic efforts.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The spectre of new confrontation between Pyongyang and Washington hangs over meetings between China, Japan and South Korea this week, with growing risks North Korean actions could end an uneasy detente and upend recent diplomatic efforts.
headline_main: North Korea Threat Looms as China, Japan, South Korea Leaders Meet
headline_print_headline: North Korea Threat Looms as China, Japan, South Korea Leaders Meet
